      "summary": "His most distinctive and dangerous feature is **sound reversal**: when his whistling sounds close, he is actually far away, but when it sounds distant, he is dangerously near.",
      "full": "His most distinctive and dangerous feature is **sound reversal**: when his whistling sounds close, he is actually far away, but when it sounds distant, he is dangerously near. El Silbón's origin involves **patricide**—he killed his father and was cursed to carry the bones forever. He hunts specific victims: **drunkards and unfaithful men**, killing them and adding their bones to his bag. Each night he counts the bones."
